        "subject": "LU-19580 gss: refresh context vs LBUG upon gss error for LDLM",
        "message": "LU-19580 gss: refresh context vs LBUG upon gss error for LDLM\n\nIf a GSS error occurs during LDLM covered page check, likely\ndue to a target failover/failback on Server side, try to\nrefresh context instead to immediatelly return and thus trigger\na LBUG for \"uncovered page!\".\n\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly testlist=sanity-sec\nTest-Parameters: kerberos=true testlist=sanity-krb5\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bfaccini@nvidia.com>\nChange-Id: I42d7722851bf3b875e0fd847ecbfc20b20894d48\n"
      },
